      <div class="msgContentFrame">No, unfortunately the nature of flyouts are such that they disappear as soon as focus is lost.  There is a delicate balance between features and the nature of having a small compact gadget.  My compromise is to use flyouts, but at the cost of being able to alway see them.  To be honest though, the elemental changes aren't that often.  Every 4 hours is the most common change in elemental influence, and we aren't even sure if that is a big influence. <br /> <br />I might be able to make another compromise, and allow you to show small icons on the main gadget page without any text.  You will have to learn which is which (I can make tool tip text appear over them) but I really don't want to make it too much larger than it already is in it's compact form. <br /> <br />I've also explored resizing the gadget dynamically, but that introduces tough hurdles and can actually freeze your entire sidebar which requires killing the .exe, manually uninstalling the gadget, and then restarting the sidebar (speaking from experiences while attempting this).  Safe to say it's better to leave it small and stable. <br /> <br />I will consider how best to make all sides happy, but I'm not sure I can <img border="0" src="http://common.zam.com/shared/smilies/smile.gif" alt="Smiley: smile"/><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm">The greatest trick the devil ever pulled was to convince the world he didn't exist. <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/wiki/FFXIV_Windows_Gadget" rel="external nofollow" title="ffxiv.zam.com/wiki/FFXIV_Windows_Gadget">Windows 7/Vista Eorzea Gadget</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?game=268&amp;mid=128102874375645847&amp;page=1" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?game=268&amp;mid=128102874375645847&amp;page=1">Keyboard LCD Eorzea Clock</a></span> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/356033.png" height="144" width="482" alt="Signature Image